The WP budget enables ODG/EVA to conduct thematic, impact and country level evaluations, to implement activities jointly with other UN agencies and to contribute to the strengthening of monitoring and evaluation capacities of counterpart ministries. During the present biennium there is a large increase in mandatory project evaluations and a need to complement ODG/EVA staff resources with consultancy services to be able to manage, GEF terminal evaluations and to ensure that UNIDO is aligned to the GEF evaluation policy and its fiduciary standards.

Preparation of a survey on the availability of alternative technologies to ozone depleting substances (ODSs)..

The overall objective of the proposed Enabling Activities (EA) is to review and update the National Implementation Plan (NIP), and have it endorsed and submitted by the government to the Conference of Parties (COP) of the Stockholm Convention. Participating stakeholders will be able to manage the additional POPs with newly developed technical skills, expertise and awareness.
Pre-ratification activities under the Minamata Convention completed to enable policy and strategic decision making and to prioritize areas for future interventions.

The main objective of institutional strengthening in eligible countries should be to provide a national institutional mechanism for co-ordinating within these countries national and international efforts for the protection of the ozone layer generally and in particular facilitate actions aimed at speedy phase-out of ozone depleting substances in the countries. (source UNEP/OzL.Pro/ExCom/7/20)

The objective of the survey is be to assist the country to better understand its consumption trends for non-ODS alternatives, and their distribution by sector and subsector. The inventory on ODS alternatives may also provide the country with an overview of their national market where ODS alternatives have been (and will be) phased in, while taking into consideration existing technologies. The survey will estimate the amounts of each ODS alternative currently used in the country, identify alternatives that could be potentially used in the future to replace HCFCs and HFCs; and forecast the amounts of each of the ODS alternatives currently used and potentially to be used in the country for the 2015-2030 period.
